              "response": "You can achieve this in Node.js using the axios library to fetch the URL and the cheerio library to parse and query the HTML. I’ll create a script that takes a URL as a command-line argument, fetches the HTML, parses it, and provides a function to extract parts of the HTML into a JSON object.\n\nFirst, I’ll add a script file and include the necessary dependencies. ",
